1
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:11,537
=The Moment I Met You=

2
00:00:11,537 --> 00:00:14,937
=Episode 17=

3
00:00:16,480 --> 00:00:17,120
Chang!

4
00:00:18,020 --> 00:00:18,960
Are you feeling better?

5
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:19,879
May I come in?

6
00:00:20,640 --> 00:00:21,320
Auntie...

7
00:00:22,039 --> 00:00:23,920
Buyu can't find out that I'm hurt.

8
00:00:25,559 --> 00:00:27,039
I can use my silver needles

9
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:29,039
to temporarily seal your meridians.

10
00:00:29,399 --> 00:00:31,719
It will stabilize
your internal injuries, but...

11
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,640
I need a little more time.

12
00:00:35,119 --> 00:00:36,039
I'll go handle him.

13
00:00:45,119 --> 00:00:45,840
Squire Mei!

14
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:47,039
Why are you here?

15
00:00:47,159 --> 00:00:47,920
Buyu.

16
00:00:48,079 --> 00:00:50,679
I heard your family was
at the Tangshan hot spring,

17
00:00:50,960 --> 00:00:53,359
so my wife and I
decided to join the fun.

18
00:00:54,399 --> 00:00:55,399
Mrs. Mei is here as well?

19
00:00:55,399 --> 00:00:56,039
She is.

20
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,200
We're paying for our own rooms.

21
00:00:59,370 --> 00:01:00,840
We certainly won't be a burden to you.

22
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:02,399
That wasn't my point.

23
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:04,280
Chang wasn't feeling well yesterday,

24
00:01:04,280 --> 00:01:05,400
so I want to check on her.

25
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:08,799
Chang isn't awake yet.

26
00:01:08,799 --> 00:01:10,439
(Premium Room Six)

27
00:01:10,439 --> 00:01:11,120
Squire Mei?

28
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:12,239
What are you doing here?

29
00:01:12,599 --> 00:01:13,239
Mei.

30
00:01:14,239 --> 00:01:16,560
We just came along for the fun.

31
00:01:17,239 --> 00:01:18,319
When did you arrive?

32
00:01:18,719 --> 00:01:19,480
Early this morning.

33
00:01:20,879 --> 00:01:22,959
Buyu, we were just about
to head to breakfast.

34
00:01:22,959 --> 00:01:24,359
Why don't you join us?

35
00:01:25,319 --> 00:01:28,040
Squire Mei, ask Chang to come along too.

36
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:29,920
Very well, I'd be honored to.

37
00:01:31,625 --> 00:01:35,750
(Premium Room Six)

38
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:56,719
Chang,

39
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:57,959
are you all right?

40
00:01:59,040 --> 00:01:59,680
I'm fine.

41
00:01:59,920 --> 00:02:01,840
I might have caught a bit of a chill

42
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:02,970
at the hot spring yesterday.

43
00:02:03,319 --> 00:02:04,680
I just feel a little weak.

44
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:07,439
But you were in your room.

45
00:02:07,439 --> 00:02:08,479
How did you get sick?

46
00:02:09,719 --> 00:02:11,680
The window must not
have been shut tight.

47
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,240
And this gentleman is...

48
00:02:16,439 --> 00:02:17,360
He is...

49
00:02:18,719 --> 00:02:20,960
I'm a distant relative
of the Chu family.

50
00:02:24,599 --> 00:02:25,439
How distant?

51
00:02:26,159 --> 00:02:27,199
A very distant branch.

52
00:02:27,599 --> 00:02:29,479
Almost no relation at all.

53
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:31,326
Exactly.

54
00:02:31,479 --> 00:02:33,599
If you're counting seniority,

55
00:02:33,599 --> 00:02:34,800
he would be my older brother.

56
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:35,960
Yes, her brother.

57
00:02:36,199 --> 00:02:37,360
I am Chu Shan.

58
00:02:37,879 --> 00:02:38,840
A pleasure to meet you.

59
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:39,479
Likewise.

60
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:42,479
What line of work are you in, Mr. Chu?

61
00:02:42,510 --> 00:02:43,719
Where do you make your living?

62
00:02:44,639 --> 00:02:46,319
I'm in the escort business.

63
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,360
I travel far and wide.

64
00:02:49,159 --> 00:02:49,840
An escort?

65
00:02:50,719 --> 00:02:52,240
Which agency do you belong to?

66
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:53,719
Well...

67
00:02:54,879 --> 00:02:55,800
I'm a freelance escort.

68
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:58,240
I don't operate
under any particular bureau.

69
00:03:08,199 --> 00:03:10,960
My dear, let's not just stand here
in the courtyard.

70
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,479
Yunchang is still unwell.

71
00:03:12,719 --> 00:03:15,599
Why don't we go inside
and chat over a meal?

72
00:03:15,599 --> 00:03:16,639
- Very well.
- All right.

73
00:03:18,039 --> 00:03:18,560
After you.

74
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:31,960
Oh, my apologies.

75
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:34,520
It's fine.

76
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:42,120
Since Ms. Yunchang isn't feeling well,

77
00:03:42,439 --> 00:03:44,800
I think she should
head back to her room and rest.

78
00:03:46,479 --> 00:03:47,240
Young man,

79
00:03:47,879 --> 00:03:49,520
I've only just arrived here.

80
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,199
I was wondering if you could

81
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,120
show me around a bit?

82
00:03:54,039 --> 00:03:54,759
What do you say?

83
00:04:06,439 --> 00:04:07,000
Certainly.

84
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,959
Chang? Chang!

85
00:04:34,820 --> 00:04:36,879
I can't break through
the blood clot at her injury.

86
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:40,360
Luo Shixun hit a vital spot

87
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,600
with those iron pellets of his.

88
00:04:42,199 --> 00:04:44,079
It has caused her
severe internal damage.

89
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:48,879
If the clot isn't cleared,
what will happen to her?

90
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,920
The clot is blocking her meridians.

91
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,079
If we can't break it,

92
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:56,079
she will lose
her martial arts skills entirely.

93
00:05:02,319 --> 00:05:04,680
Is there any way to save her?

94
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:06,680
There is.

95
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:09,800
A Thousand-year Lingzhi could heal her.

96
00:05:10,079 --> 00:05:11,120
A Thousand-year Lingzhi?

97
00:05:12,639 --> 00:05:15,800
Any Lingzhi is hard enough to find,
let alone one that old.

98
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,839
Where would we even look?

99
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:19,680
The palace?

100
00:05:20,879 --> 00:05:21,759
From what I know,

101
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:24,360
Changle Hall here
in the Capital has one.

102
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:25,720
Go and get it now.

103
00:05:26,319 --> 00:05:28,680
But that Lingzhi
is their greatest treasure.

104
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,720
They wouldn't sell it.

105
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,680
Well, just pay them more.

106
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,759
It isn't a matter of price.

107
00:05:32,759 --> 00:05:33,970
They simply refuse to sell it.

108
00:05:46,639 --> 00:05:49,120
Do you love Yunchang a lot?

109
00:05:49,439 --> 00:05:50,040
Yes.

110
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:52,079
What kind of love?

111
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:54,439
A love that remains unchanging
until the end of time.

112
00:05:57,319 --> 00:06:02,240
Then, regardless of whether
she is wealthy or penniless,

113
00:06:02,839 --> 00:06:04,759
infirm or aged,

114
00:06:05,519 --> 00:06:07,160
will your heart remain exactly the same?

115
00:06:07,639 --> 00:06:08,290
Without a doubt.

116
00:06:09,279 --> 00:06:09,920
Sir,

117
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:12,000
I have two questions for you.

118
00:06:12,639 --> 00:06:13,240
Go ahead.

119
00:06:15,650 --> 00:06:17,349
You're the true Jade Squirrel,
aren't you?

120
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,319
And what if I am?

121
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:25,399
And what if I am not?

122
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,759
If you really are the Jade Squirrel,

123
00:06:28,399 --> 00:06:29,639
it is my duty to bring you in.

124
00:06:30,330 --> 00:06:31,920
Don't you care about marrying Yunchang?

125
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:32,680
Of course I do.

126
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:34,839
Once I arrest you,

127
00:06:35,959 --> 00:06:37,639
I will explain everything to Chang.

128
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:40,279
If she can't forgive me,

129
00:06:41,959 --> 00:06:43,199
then I shall never marry.

130
00:06:43,879 --> 00:06:45,439
I'll watch over her in silence.

131
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:52,360
You give me far too much credit.

132
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:57,000
I am nothing more than
a lowly distant relative.

133
00:06:57,439 --> 00:07:00,360
As for "Thieving Cat"
or "Jade Squirrel,"

134
00:07:01,010 --> 00:07:03,160
I haven't the faintest idea
what you're talking about.

135
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,560
Where were you last night?

136
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,000
On the road to get here.

137
00:07:10,439 --> 00:07:11,839
Before you arrived,

138
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,800
I found myself baffled.

139
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,600
Why does the Chu family
resent the Gate Bureau?

140
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:20,079
And why every time
the Jade Squirrel surfaces,

141
00:07:20,879 --> 00:07:22,120
Chang somehow gets involved?

142
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,399
What have you concluded?

143
00:07:24,519 --> 00:07:25,720
It all traces back to you.

144
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:28,319
They're all just trying to shield you.

145
00:07:33,262 --> 00:07:36,981
I'm impressed by your imagination,
Constable Mao.

146
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:38,600
Pity, though.

147
00:07:39,879 --> 00:07:41,319
You lack any actual proof.

148
00:07:43,839 --> 00:07:44,519
That's true.

149
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:46,759
I don't have any evidence at the moment.

150
00:07:47,580 --> 00:07:49,399
I have no choice
but to take you at your word.

151
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,639
But don't think that
you can play me for a fool.

152
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:54,120
You'd better not harm Chang.

153
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,399
The feeling is mutual.

154
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:03,920
(I may not know
if you're the true Jade Squirrel,)

155
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:07,839
(but I'm certain you're involved
with them somehow.)

156
00:08:19,450 --> 00:08:20,089
Chang.

157
00:08:20,759 --> 00:08:22,160
How did you get worse overnight?

158
00:08:23,639 --> 00:08:25,079
It's just a common cold.

159
00:08:25,199 --> 00:08:26,399
I'll be fine in a few days.

160
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:30,800
There's something I need to ask you.

161
00:08:31,759 --> 00:08:32,519
What is it?

162
00:08:32,919 --> 00:08:34,799
What is your relationship with Chu Shan?

163
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:39,559
He really is just a distant relative.

164
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:41,600
A distant relative?

165
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,480
He seems too concerned about you

166
00:08:44,879 --> 00:08:46,200
to be just a distant relative.

167
00:08:47,210 --> 00:08:48,370
Did he give you a hard time?

168
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:50,799
Not exactly.

169
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:53,679
He just kept questioning me
to see how I truly felt about you.

170
00:08:57,399 --> 00:08:58,799
That is just how he is.

171
00:08:58,799 --> 00:09:00,080
Don't take it to heart.

172
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:02,840
He's likely just
being overprotective of me.

173
00:09:03,679 --> 00:09:04,840
We may be distant relatives,

174
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,440
but we have always been quite close.

175
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:11,440
Still, I find his background
rather suspicious.

176
00:09:13,919 --> 00:09:15,480
An occupational hazard for constables!

177
00:09:15,639 --> 00:09:16,279
Mao Buyu,

178
00:09:16,399 --> 00:09:17,559
one relative shows up and

179
00:09:17,559 --> 00:09:18,879
you're being paranoid.

180
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,480
What, do you trust me that little?

181
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,679
Should I show you the family tree?

182
00:09:21,679 --> 00:09:22,240
No, no!

183
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:23,879
My dear, I was wrong.

184
00:09:24,340 --> 00:09:25,519
Please don't be cross with me.

185
00:09:29,860 --> 00:09:31,480
Chu Xiangshan,
get out here this instant!

186
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:33,919
Coming, I'm coming!

187
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:36,519
What is the matter?

188
00:09:38,340 --> 00:09:39,279
Where is Chu Xiangshan?

189
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:40,919
Where did he go?

190
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,799
Buyu and I finally get to be together.

191
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:47,399
Is he trying to ruin everything
the moment he returns?

192
00:09:49,399 --> 00:09:51,559
He left quite a while ago.

193
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:54,080
Find him and bring him back!

194
00:09:57,759 --> 00:09:58,960
Chang! Chang!

195
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:00,600
- You're all here?
- Where have you been?

196
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,200
Chang,

197
00:10:01,759 --> 00:10:04,639
I've brought back
the Thousand-year Lingzhi for you!

198
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:09,600
Sir,

199
00:10:10,399 --> 00:10:12,159
someone purchased
a Thousand-year Lingzhi

200
00:10:12,159 --> 00:10:13,600
from Changle Hall.

201
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:15,639
When did this happen?

202
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:16,840
Just today.

203
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:27,879
Are you even aware of our rules?

204
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:30,399
My girl,

205
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:32,360
I've brought you the medicine you need.

206
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:34,840
What does that
have to do with sect rules?

207
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,990
I spent seven years
disciplining my subordinates,

208
00:10:37,679 --> 00:10:38,440
and now you've gone

209
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:39,600
and ruined it all.

210
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,320
Who told you to steal?

211
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:43,039
Brother,

212
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:44,320
you didn't know.

213
00:10:44,639 --> 00:10:46,279
Ever since Chang became Sect Leader,

214
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:47,380
she's established a new law.

215
00:10:47,399 --> 00:10:49,720
The Sacred Hand Sect is
no longer allowed to steal.

216
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:52,120
Do you really have
so little faith in me?

217
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:54,279
It's not that I don't trust you.

218
00:10:54,279 --> 00:10:55,559
But you're always so reckless!

219
00:10:55,639 --> 00:10:56,519
Reckless?

220
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:58,919
I got this Thousand-year Lingzhi

221
00:10:58,919 --> 00:11:00,360
for you.

222
00:11:00,519 --> 00:11:01,320
Besides...

223
00:11:01,320 --> 00:11:02,720
You say that now,

224
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,879
but why did you abandon me and leave?

225
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,520
You come and go whenever it suits you.

226
00:11:07,039 --> 00:11:08,480
Have you no sense of responsibility?

227
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,279
Get rid of this Lingzhi.

228
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,919
I don't want stolen herbs.

229
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:15,320
Chang,

230
00:11:15,879 --> 00:11:17,320
that's enough.

231
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:19,159
Yunchang is right.

232
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:21,720
As a father,

233
00:11:22,159 --> 00:11:23,320
I have been irresponsible.

234
00:11:27,159 --> 00:11:28,159
Fine.

235
00:11:28,919 --> 00:11:30,440
Since you've admitted your mistake,

236
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,519
I'll give you one more chance.

237
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:33,440
There is no need.

238
00:11:34,799 --> 00:11:36,440
As a subordinate
of the Sacred Hand Sect,

239
00:11:37,399 --> 00:11:38,720
I have defied the Sect Leader.

240
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:43,240
I am resigning from the sect.

241
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:45,799
But...

242
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:46,639
Brother,

243
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:48,799
isn't this a bit too extreme?

244
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:51,360
It's fine.

245
00:11:51,679 --> 00:11:52,639
Uncle, let him.

246
00:11:52,639 --> 00:11:53,639
If this is his choice,

247
00:11:53,639 --> 00:11:54,679
then I will respect it.

248
00:11:55,559 --> 00:11:57,159
I bet you only see me as a burden.

249
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:58,012
Now that you have

250
00:11:58,012 --> 00:11:59,453
a convenient excuse to be rid of me,

251
00:12:01,090 --> 00:12:02,240
you didn't hesitate at all.

252
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,662
Chang! Where are you going?

253
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,240
Go talk to her.

254
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:15,519
Why didn't you say something earlier?

255
00:12:16,759 --> 00:12:17,840
I wanted to,

256
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:20,200
but I was at a complete loss for words.

257
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,519
You know my brother.

258
00:12:23,159 --> 00:12:24,879
He's always been headstrong

259
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,559
and inconsiderate.

260
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,159
But this time,

261
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,399
his intentions really were for the best.

262
00:12:31,519 --> 00:12:33,120
I suspect he spoke that way today

263
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,240
because he realized the Mao family

264
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,720
is already suspicious of him.

265
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:39,200
If he stays here

266
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:40,720
and happens to slip up,

267
00:12:40,799 --> 00:12:41,919
the consequences are dire.

268
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:46,279
But family is still family.

269
00:12:47,279 --> 00:12:48,120
I think

270
00:12:49,519 --> 00:12:50,799
you should go see him off.

271
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:15,519
Mao Buyu,

272
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:17,039
treat Chu Yunchang well.

273
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:18,559
You won't regret it.

274
00:13:21,350 --> 00:13:23,237
(Embroidered Guard,
Unit of Commander Zhuang)

275
00:13:26,125 --> 00:13:27,240
(Embroidered Guard, Commander Mao Buyu
of the North Pacification Office)

276
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:28,120
(Embroidered Guard?)

277
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,759
(Who are you exactly?)

278
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:35,600
Brother.

279
00:13:51,287 --> 00:13:52,737
(Pawn Ticket, Chu Xiangshan)

280
00:13:55,150 --> 00:13:56,212
(Pawn Ticket, Chu Xiangshan)

281
00:13:59,475 --> 00:14:00,480
(Pawned for a thousand taels of silver)
(Pawn tickets?)

282
00:14:07,787 --> 00:14:09,242
(Items: Jade pendant,
antique fan, jade bracelet)

283
00:14:09,243 --> 00:14:10,775
(Blue-and-white pottery, one mu of land,
a thousand taels of silver)

284
00:14:16,279 --> 00:14:18,360
I've made some inquiries.

285
00:14:20,159 --> 00:14:22,559
It turns out Manager Shen
of Changle Hall

286
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:24,180
owed your father a favor from years ago.

287
00:14:24,799 --> 00:14:26,840
When your father went
to ask for the herb,

288
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:27,840
he didn't dare refuse.

289
00:14:29,799 --> 00:14:30,600
But after all,

290
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,680
that Lingzhi was Changle Hall's
greatest treasure.

291
00:14:33,399 --> 00:14:36,320
So he named a staggering price.

292
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:39,879
Your father hasn't saved much

293
00:14:40,090 --> 00:14:41,639
during his years in the Martial World.

294
00:14:42,279 --> 00:14:43,610
He had to sell off his possessions

295
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,399
to scrape the money together.

296
00:14:47,559 --> 00:14:48,960
When your father left,

297
00:14:49,519 --> 00:14:50,480
he told me

298
00:14:50,799 --> 00:14:53,200
to grind the Lingzhi into a powder,

299
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:54,559
mix it into your medicine,

300
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,399
and feed it to you personally.

301
00:14:58,039 --> 00:15:01,480
Since you both care
for each other so much,

302
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,100
why go through all this?

303
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:06,590
If he wants to go,

304
00:15:07,159 --> 00:15:08,320
how could I possibly stop him?

305
00:15:09,559 --> 00:15:10,559
My girl,

306
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,799
you even managed a family of constables

307
00:15:12,799 --> 00:15:13,759
like Mao Buyu's.

308
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:15,759
Why lose your composure

309
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:17,399
when it comes to your own father?

310
00:15:17,519 --> 00:15:18,320
He's right.

311
00:15:18,679 --> 00:15:19,399
Indeed.

312
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:35,320
Who bought the Thousand-year Lingzhi?

313
00:15:38,279 --> 00:15:38,879
Speak!

314
00:15:39,960 --> 00:15:41,679
Take a good look. Which one was it?

315
00:15:44,639 --> 00:15:45,600
It was none of them.

316
00:15:51,519 --> 00:15:53,390
I suggest you think carefully
before answering.

317
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:56,200
It really wasn't any of them.

318
00:15:56,559 --> 00:15:58,120
The man is an old acquaintance.

319
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:00,519
Years ago,
while I was selling herbs in Shandong,

320
00:16:00,519 --> 00:16:01,600
I was ambushed by bandits.

321
00:16:01,679 --> 00:16:03,399
He's the one who saved my life.

322
00:16:03,399 --> 00:16:05,200
I don't know his name.

323
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:11,879
He...

324
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,519
He looked quite a bit older

325
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,200
than this portrait.

326
00:16:18,159 --> 00:16:19,360
I'm telling the truth.

327
00:16:23,799 --> 00:16:25,679
Did he mention where he came from?

328
00:16:27,399 --> 00:16:28,720
Where he was from?

329
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:32,480
Where was it?

330
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:38,320
I remember now!

331
00:16:38,639 --> 00:16:41,200
He seemed to mention Tang...

332
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,519
Tangshan Hot Spring, yes!

333
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:55,225
♪Grudges and regrets
are like strong wine♪

334
00:16:55,263 --> 00:16:58,138
♪Drink it down and let it go♪

335
00:16:58,638 --> 00:17:04,356
♪An empty cup for our love and hate♪

336
00:17:05,538 --> 00:17:08,858
♪Tears blur a fate I can't control♪

337
00:17:08,988 --> 00:17:11,908
♪Let's drink until dawn♪

338
00:17:13,076 --> 00:17:18,316
♪Behind this mask, I'll never lie♪

339
00:17:19,538 --> 00:17:21,931
♪Every reunion feels like the first♪

340
00:17:21,931 --> 00:17:25,581
♪This hidden smile will never fade♪

341
00:17:25,650 --> 00:17:29,140
♪One heart, standing by your side♪

342
00:17:29,238 --> 00:17:32,213
♪To the ends of time♪

343
00:17:32,213 --> 00:17:35,588
♪The moon traces your face♪

344
00:17:35,775 --> 00:17:39,363
♪Draped in clouds, you fill my heart♪

345
00:17:39,363 --> 00:17:45,603
♪To find you
and keep our promise forever♪

346
00:17:45,938 --> 00:17:49,153
♪A silent prayer in my soul♪

347
00:17:49,438 --> 00:17:52,976
♪Carrying my vow beneath the moon♪

348
00:17:53,263 --> 00:17:56,288
♪Hoping we never drift apart again♪

349
00:17:56,288 --> 00:17:59,388
♪On our way to forever♪

350
00:17:59,388 --> 00:18:03,238
♪The moon traces your face♪

351
00:18:03,238 --> 00:18:06,598
♪Draped in clouds, you fill my heart♪

352
00:18:06,788 --> 00:18:12,748
♪To find you
and keep our promise forever♪

353
00:18:13,825 --> 00:18:23,465
♪Just to be with you♪
